&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dementia and Delirium Clinical Nurse Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for the right person to undertake the role of Dementia and Delirium CNS within the safeguarding adults team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is one of three such roles responsible for providing expert advice, care and support to staff patients with dementia and their carers. The post holder will also work within the Guy’s Memory Service with patients who have newly been diagnosed with dementia. The successful candidate will work closely with the Dementia and Delirium (DaD) team which is a multi-disciplinary team in the care of people with dementia and or delirium.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Dementia and Delirium Clinical Nurse Specialists work as part of the wider Trust safeguarding adults team, helping to ensure safer care for our most vulnerable patients. If you have a passion for delivering good nursing care and enjoy working with people with a dementia and or delirium and their carers, this will be the ideal job for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 08th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: 23rd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal chat or visit to the Trust please contact Mala Karasu on 020 7188 9186 or email mala.karasu@gstt.nhs.uk. We want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
